---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title="Family Settings: Parental Controls & Safe Laptops - LaptopVette" description="How to configure family safety and parental controls across Windows, macOS, and ChromeOS. Practical tips for families and shared devices." path="/guides/family-settings" type="article" />
</head>
<body>

  <nav class="navbar">
    <div class="container"><a href="/" class="logo">Laptop<span>Vette</span></a></div>
  </nav>

  <article class="article-container">
    <h1>Family Settings: Parental Controls & Shared Device Best Practices</h1>
    <p>Setting up laptops for families involves more than just buying durable hardware — it requires configuring the device so parents can manage access, protect privacy, and ensure safe browsing for children.</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Why family settings matter</h2>
      <p>Family settings help you control what children access, limit screen time, and protect personal data. They also make it easy to enforce healthy device use across multiple devices in the household.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Windows: Family Safety</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Create Microsoft family accounts and configure activity reporting.</li>
        <li>Set screen time, content filters, and app/game restrictions per child account.</li>
        <li>Use "Find my device" and device encryption for safety and theft protection.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>ChromeOS: Supervised Use & Simplicity</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Use Google Family Link to manage supervised accounts, set bedtime limits, and review apps.</li>
        <li>Chromebooks are often easier to maintain for younger users because of automatic updates and sandboxing.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>macOS: Parental Controls & Screen Time</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Configure Screen Time via Family Sharing to set downtime and content limits.</li>
        <li>Use strong passcodes/passwords and keep macOS updated to maintain security.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Hardware & Practical Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Choose durable chassis and consider protective cases for young children.</li>
        <li>Prefer models with long battery life to avoid daily charging friction.</li>
        <li>Use account separation (one account per family member) to keep data and settings clean.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top:20px;">For device-specific setup walk-throughs, consult the OEM support pages or reach out if you'd like step-by-step guides for a particular laptop model.</p>
  </article>

  <style>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; background-color: #f8fafc; color: #0f172a; line-height: 1.85; }
    .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px; }
    
    /* Navigation */
    .navbar { background: #ffffff; border-bottom: 1px solid #d1d5db; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; }
    .navbar .container { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; height: 70px; }
    .logo { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; color: #0f172a; text-decoration: none; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
    .logo span { color: #b91c1c; }
    
    /* Article Container */
    .article-container { max-width: 840px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 40px; background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 12px; }
    .article-container h1 { font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.25; color: #0f172a; }
    .article-container > p { margin-bottom: 1.4em; line-height: 1.85; text-align: justify; }
    .article-container h2 { font-size: 22px; margin: 56px 0 22px 0; border-left: 4px solid #b91c1c; padding-left: 15px; }
    .article-container section { margin-bottom: 2em; }
    .article-container ul { list-style: disc inside; }
    .article-container li { margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1.6; }
  </style>
</body>
</html>
